org.matsim.contrib.freight.jsprit

Class NetworkBasedTransportCosts

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.matsim.contrib.freight.jsprit.NetworkBasedTransportCosts
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.graphhopper.jsprit.core.problem.cost.BackwardTransportCost, com.graphhopper.jsprit.core.problem.cost.BackwardTransportTime, com.graphhopper.jsprit.core.problem.cost.ForwardTransportCost, com.graphhopper.jsprit.core.problem.cost.ForwardTransportTime, com.graphhopper.jsprit.core.problem.cost.TransportCost, com.graphhopper.jsprit.core.problem.cost.TransportTime, com.graphhopper.jsprit.core.problem.cost.VehicleRoutingTransportCosts

    public class NetworkBasedTransportCosts
extends Object
implements com.graphhopper.jsprit.core.problem.cost.VehicleRoutingTransportCosts
    This calculates transport-times and transport-costs to cover the distance from one location to another. It calculates these values based on a Network to serve as VehicleRoutingTransportCosts in the VehicleRoutingProblem.

    It can be used with multiple threads. Note that each thread gets its own leastCostPathCalculator. It is created only once and cached afterwards. Thus it requires a threadSafe leastCostPathCalculatorFactory (the calculator itself does not need to be thread-safe).

    If the client of this class requests cost-information to get from from-location to to-location at a certain time and with a certain vehicle, it looks up whether there is already an entry in the cache. If so, it returns the cached value, if not it calculates new values with a leastCostPathCalculator defined in here. It looks up the cached values according to the TransportDataKey.

    Two TransportDataKeys are equal if the following data are equal
    - from-locations
    - to-locations
    - time and
    - vehicleTypes

    Keep in mind that if you have many locations, small time-bins and many vehicleTypes, calculations get very time- and memory-consuming.

      • getTransportTime

        public double getTransportTime(com.graphhopper.jsprit.core.problem.Location fromId,
                               com.graphhopper.jsprit.core.problem.Location toId,
                               double departureTime,
                               com.graphhopper.jsprit.core.problem.driver.Driver driver,
                               com.graphhopper.jsprit.core.problem.vehicle.Vehicle vehicle)
        Gets the transport-time.

        If fromId.equals(toId) it returns 0.0. Otherwise, it looks up in the cache whether the transport-time has already been computed (see TransportDataKey, TransportData). If so, it returns the cached travel-time. If not, it computes and caches new values with the leastCostPathCalc defined in here.
